<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<qti-assessment-item
    xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0p1_v1p0.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/mathml/v3p0/schema/xsd/mathml3.xsd"
    identifier="pythagorean-theorem-ab-length"
    title="Length of Hypotenuse in a Right Triangle"
    time-dependent="false"
    xml:lang="en-US">

    <qti-response-declaration base-type="identifier" cardinality="single" identifier="RESPONSE">
        <qti-correct-response>
            <qti-value>B</qti-value>
        </qti-correct-response>
    </qti-response-declaration>


    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>

    <qti-item-body>
        <div id="reference_text">
            <img src="https://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-graphie/6d78801643a529e913c995e81124b1f3cad8c282.svg"
                 alt="Triangle ABC has right angle C. Side AC has a length of 7, and side BC has a length of 6."
                 width="356"
                 height="400"/>
        </div>
        <p>In the right triangle shown, the length of 
            <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                    <mover accent="true">
                        <mrow>
                            <mi>A</mi>
                            <mi>C</mi>
                        </mrow>
                        <mo>&#xaf;</mo>
                    </mover>
                    <mo>=</mo>
                    <mn>7</mn>
                </mrow>
            </math> and the length of 
            <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                    <mover accent="true">
                        <mrow>
                            <mi>B</mi>
                            <mi>C</mi>
                        </mrow>
                        <mo>&#xaf;</mo>
                    </mover>
                    <mo>=</mo>
                    <mn>6</mn>
                </mrow>
            </math>.
        </p>
        
        <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
            <qti-prompt>What is the length of 
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mover accent="true">
                        <mrow>
                            <mi>A</mi>
                            <mi>B</mi>
                        </mrow>
                        <mo>&#xaf;</mo>
                    </mover>
                </math> ?
            </qti-prompt>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="A">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msqrt><mn>13</mn></msqrt></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="A">You may have forgotten to square the lengths of the legs.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="B">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msqrt><mn>85</mn></msqrt></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="B">Correct! Using the Pythagorean theorem: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>AB</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>AC</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>BC</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>85</mn></math>, so <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>85</mn></msqrt></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="C">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>13</mn></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="C">You might have added the legs directly without squaring them. The Pythagorean theorem requires squaring first: a² + b² = c².</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="D">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>85</mn></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="D">You forgot to take the square root. This is the value of AB², not AB.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
        </qti-choice-interaction>
        
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="CORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> You properly applied the Pythagorean theorem: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>AB</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>85</mn></math>, so <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>85</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="INCORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Not quite.</strong> For a right triangle with legs of length <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>7</mn></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>6</mn></math>, use the Pythagorean theorem: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. So <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>AB</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>85</mn></math>. Don't forget to take the square root: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>85</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
    </qti-item-body>

    <qti-response-processing template="https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/rptemplates/match_correct"/>

</qti-assessment-item>